	(6802,107,'wpcf-biography','Hello, my name is Viktoria Hristova. I\'m born on October 28th, 1989 in Varna, Bulgaria. \r\n     In school I have received numerous certificates of acknowledgment for my artistic abilities, I have participated in a great amount of art exhibitions hosted by my school and have won several awards. With my traveling and exploring I became very interested in the unique qualities of every place. \r\n     I have done a lot of experimenting with different art materials and understand how they mix together. I especially enjoy to do colages because they include a process that is not traditional and result in an abstract piece of art. However I love to combine materials and rarely limit the artpiece to a single material.\r\n     The computer programs that I use to help my designs are Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Illustrator, 3DS Max, Autodesk Maya, and GoogleSketchup. I am currently learning Unity3D.'),
