	(8128,563,'wpcf-short-description','sound sculpture about distance and relation'),
	(8129,563,'wpcf-long-description','“You, them and the space in between” is a sound sculpture about revealing the relationship between emerging systems and us.\r\nIt showcases a network, which changes over time. In my thesis I create a soundscape, which represents the emergent network. I am using different sounds as the metaphor of animals, which inhabit the soundscape.\r\nThe change between the animals and their environment show a dynamic process. This change is based on the distance of the audience to the object itself. \r\nThe dynamic relationship is a meditation on sound performance and the connotation of interactivity.'),
