	(9152,540,'wpcf-short-description','An installation which enables the audience to capture the ephemeral process of handwriting.'),
	(9153,540,'wpcf-long-description','The aim of my project is to capture the dynamic movements in the process of producing an analog handwritten message, and transfer this one-time process into a (permanent) digital printing. The printing thus becomes an unique piece of mediated memory which only belongs to this ephemeral experience. \r\n\r\n	A person’s handwriting is an unique visual signature which contains not only the linguistic contents, but also the affection toward the message receiver. However, we are seldom aware of our emotions and mental statements behind the writing process, and we are not able to capture or see this experience through regular writing practice. Though the digital improvements of technology have seemed to replace handwriting as a major communicating way, the uniqueness of handwriting and intimate affection toward another person behind a writing process still can not be replaced through digital platform. However, the assistance of technology enables the possibilities of capturing those invisible uniqueness and writing process, which is not able to show in traditional handwriting format. \r\n\r\n	In this project, the process of handwriting is translated into a graphical information analysis, creates a relationship between analog and digital writing styles, and also offers a chance for its users to understand the beauty of a traditional methodology in digital age.'),
