	(11826,566,'wpcf-short-description','A series of mini projects that is around the topic Procrastination. A digital solution - an iphone app and a physical design(print)'),
	(11827,566,'wpcf-long-description','During my research, I was working with an online support group for procrastinators. It is very often that people seek out for help and land here in our support group. For a lot of times I observe people in our online group trying to form a pact with someone and help each other. Usually procrastination behavior is more severe when you are by yourself. People make excuses for themselves, and they easily fall for it. But with a partner, they can support it each other during the rough time, and check on each other. And making a promise to yourself is easy to break, when it involves another person, that provide some motivation, like you don’t to disappoint your partner, you want to live up to people’s expectation, etc.\r\n\r\nThis iteration of my project is about providing a way for people to form such pact and keep it working. The idea is the users are the project manager for each other. They have responsibility for their partner. On the main view, it is a timeline calendar for two people as pact. They can post their working schedule to this mutual calendar. And for each calendar event, we called it a task. Different from a normal calendar event, there is an option to set your checkpoint. When you finished, you post your outcome to a checkpoint for your partner to check your progress. It could be an url, or other online presence, or set to custom, which you check it by communication.\r\n\r\nWith my research, putting your working plan down for other to see is very important for procrastinator to overcome this problem. It is a symbol of making a commitment, and making it public to other people not just themselves is making things more real, more formal.\r\n\r\nIt is even more helpful when you can work with someone simultaneously. That is breaking the solitude and add more pressure and threshold for you to bail. And fighting together is motivating each other to keep it going. I designed a customized event called mutual event, which you can set up by toggle the “invitation” button when you add the event to your timeline. It will send an invitation to your partner, and when he approve it, it will add this event to both of your calendar as a mutual event. When that event happens, you and your partner will be working together simultaneously on your own project. And you check on each other’s project during or right after that event.'),
