	(12279,543,'wpcf-short-description','A series of objects discussing hidden stories of electronic waste.'),
	(12280,543,'wpcf-long-description','When the technology of an infrastructure is truly successful, it is least noticed of all. This phenomenon is called ‘black boxing’. Over the last decades devices have turned into these black boxes quite literally as the technology inside changed from mechanical to electronic and continues to reduce in size. Only when the device breaks does the technology become visible to us again, this interruption unboxes that black box. But at that point, when the technology has always hidden itself from view, the user of the infrastructure has a hard time even recognizing the option of repair.\r\n\r\n\'Two or Three Things\' is an exhibition that creates the interruption in our perception that unboxes the black box by exploring the technology inside of our devices, bringing back attention to that materiality and by finding out what happens after we throw our technology out.'),
