	(12702,506,'wpcf-short-description','Data Rush is an internet-connected kinetic sculpture that explores the crisis about data.'),
	(12703,506,'wpcf-long-description','Data Rush is an interactive kinetic sculpture that reflects the past, the present, and the future of our data over the internet. Specifically, it talks about the underlying keys how giant internet corporates in Silicon Valley monopolize and leverage user information in many ways, since they have discovered that the value of user information is unimaginable. Above and beyond, it captures the growing awareness of today’s internet users about the evolving mass electronic surveillance program on the internet such as PRISM and X-Keyscore. Therefore, every pieces of our information we send and receive – the data we rush out – are monetized and become tools against us. \r\n\r\nData Rush was inspired by the other “rush” in 19th century – the gold rush in California, near Silicon Valley of the present day. The sculpture itself represents a big intricate processing machine. By tapping into data in the network, turning them into a mechanism for dropping gold (candy) – in other words – exchanging bytes with real currency.'),
