	(14642,522,'wpcf-short-description','Children\'s Interactive Book'),
	(14643,522,'wpcf-long-description','I am driven to help children make sense of the complexities and realities of the adult world. Basic, fundamental concepts of democracy, human rights and freedom are often taught as abstract and technical ideas, but hardly ever taught in practical ones: real world examples that children can grasp and understand. The idea is to teach young minds these concepts in such a way as to correlate with the ‘real world’ by framing these ideas in an approachable as well as novel fashion.\r\n\r\nIn countries where these concepts are restricted, censored and sometimes even non existent, children can grow up without taking the time to question their rights, thinking that the status quo is as it is, because it has always been that way. However, what if they could understand from a young age that their voice is important, that they are meant to be heard, and that an idea can change perspectives?\r\n\r\nI am making an interactive book for children with the goal of helping them to understand basic concepts of democracy and encourage them to use their voice.'),
