	(14951,85,'wpcf-biography','Morgan is a creature of curiosity and creativity and challenge. Having grown up in Asia, Morgan settled back home in Sydney Australia to finish her schooling, where she completed the International Baccalaureate. Drawing from both her international and artistic upbringing, she initially she studied languages and art history at Sydney University. However a yearning for more tangible creativity lead her to transfer to Sydney College of the Arts where she received a Degree in Visual Arts majoring in Film in Digital Art. During her time at SCA Morgan was the first student to be elected to take part in a semester-long exchange program with Parsons the New School for Design in New York. She fell in love. With the college. With the city. With it all. Upon graduating from SCA Morgan was awarded a scholarship to do her Masters back at Parsons, expanding her storytelling into new territory through the Design and Technology program. With her thesis taking on the highly controversial subject of DMT, in a multimedia form that incorporates film, a large-scale sculptural installation and an iPad app, Morgan looks forward to where her work takes her from here.'),
