	(15102,109,'wpcf-long-description','Starry City is a light installation experimentally exploring human self-cognition, perception, definition and dreams by the metaphor of stars and city light.\r\n\r\nWe are lighting up the night to make it as bright as day. For our instinctive fear of unknown danger and the possibility of getting lost in darkness. But when we try our best to drive out the darkness and we think we have overcome it and will never get lost,\r\nwe abandon the star light at the same time, who acts as a guide at dark night physically and spiritually. \r\n\r\nThe light only shines when the darkness exists, and we will ultimately find ourselves lose in light.'),
