	(15887,534,'wpcf-short-description','An interactive web base mystery game about loneliness and companionship'),
	(15888,534,'wpcf-long-description','\"Gone\" is a web-based mystery game that raises questions about loneliness and companionship. Users are invited to the interface with an opening of a Chinese student missing for a month and no one knows where she went and why. The mission is to find the reasons why she\'s gone according to the conversations with related connections she had. Users can pick questions to ask the target to find clues according to the answers. The game will lead to an open-ended result to leave rooms for players to expand their imaginations. The core of the project is to remind audience’s own circumstances in society, friendship, love and loneliness. Using a game engages more people who might have no interests in social cultural topics to involve more spontaneously. The narrative of this game will be fictional but based on real stories collected from international students who are experiencing similar issues. What shows on the interface can be real and unreal simultaneously. No matter what the credibility is, it definitely reflects the value of life that people possibly have.'),
