	(16809,537,'wpcf-short-description','An exploration to use code as vehicle to teach math concepts'),
	(16810,537,'wpcf-long-description','Code for math is an “exploration” in the similarities that Code and Math have. It seeks to explore connections between the two topics. Coding shows the potential of the instrumentality that Math can have, by providing an immediate feedback of the math used, it gives people the possibility to see applications that Math has.\r\n\r\nFor many years, the way that we learn Math at school hasn\'t changed. A repetition process of writing equations and solving exercises on paper hasn\'t changed in the last 20 years. It also raises the question of how educators without having access to technology can enable new ways of learning. The similarities that Math and Code have, present an opportunity to explore different ways in the learning process, Code an Logic as an extension of Algebra give the opportunity to explore Math from a self-expression approach.\r\n\r\nFor this thesis outcome, the idea was to create a series of mini exercises that build on top of each other. Variables, Cartesian plane and Functions were the chosen topics. With the use of intuitive and interactive elements. Users have a better understanding and more practical of the concepts. This, will serve as a milestone to start developing Highschool curriculum to serve as a complement to regular Math classes.'),
