	(16973,501,'wpcf-short-description','Spies, Prophets, Programmers, Visions, Boolean Logic, Suspense, Artificial Intelligence, Gods & Goddesses'),
	(16974,501,'wpcf-long-description','What began as an inquiry into the highly questionable operations of government surveillance and the methods of a data driven market-economy, comes an exploration of our relationship with the whole digital information apparatus. The information is now the ultimate telos, rather than being an extension and tool for our individuality. A new mythology has arisen, conceived by the forebearers of digital technology and we are their followers. When the Information is found, it is perceived as an infinite source of narratological enlightenment. It is the well of life, promising to bestow many blessings for us and posterity. We were in bondage to a state of ignorance, but a new humanity has been consecrated to this digital will. These considerations involve how digital information has become the holy grail for the interests of corporate, political and personal gain.\r\n      \r\nProject 1: NSAphorism is a project that aims to express the contradictory notion of domestic surveillance with the aphorism; the folk wisdom of a society. It is a critical outlook on a representative government\'s domestic spying methods in relationship to our private data existing in the virtual agora. \r\n\r\nProject 2: IO - Information Oracle, is an artificial intelligence and mediator of the data mythos. Using a binary divination system, she interprets the signs in a person\'s digital input. She is also a revealer of the pantheon of new deities and speaks to us of the origins of the Information Age.'),
