	(16990,42,'wpcf-biography','Albert is a designer, creative technologist and artist located in NYC. Born and raised in San Francisco, his affinity for the arts was found manifest at an early age. In 2006, he came to New York after art school, where he worked as a graphic designer and artist. For four years, he painted and fabricated stenciling methods for Jeff Koons. He traveled to Europe last fall for the first time, where he exhibited an interactive art installation at the RE-NEW conference in Copenhagen. His work as of late includes interactive experiences, web projects, and pieces that engage with the implications of our data-driven environment.'),
